<p>In the latest development, Pakistan announced that four days of truce negotiations with Afghanistan’s Taliban in Istanbul ended without a workable solution, after talks brokered by Qatar and Turkey . Islamabad framed the talks as aimed at stopping cross-border attacks and pressed for action against the Tehreek-e-Taliban Pakistan (TTP), while Afghan authorities have rejected accusations of harbouring Pakistani militants . The collapse comes after heavy fighting along the shared frontier earlier in October and raises concerns about a renewed escalation between the neighbours .</p><img src='https://kagiproxy.com/img/zHUKu01KDIytaBo6zLW-yxhISOcCLRiOBfsMVzI2Cmo7fLHjaXbu5YZsejW97QOdCev28c5SVPgbKO9o512yTJObYQYetwiBygTz8ilHmBT5' alt='Information Minister Attaullah Tarar speaks to the media in August 2025 — DawnNewsTV' /><br /><h3>Highlights:</h3><ul><li>Security demands: Pakistan repeatedly demanded dismantling of militant sanctuaries and action against the TTP as a precondition for a long-term truce</li><li>Mediator role: Turkey and Qatar hosted and helped broker talks in Istanbul after a prior Doha round that produced a temporary ceasefire, showing continued third‑party engagement</li><li>Core sticking points: Negotiators clashed over removal of TTP safe havens, drone strikes and mutual mistrust — issues analysts warn could reignite wider conflict</li><li>Escalatory rhetoric: Pakistan’s information minister accused Kabul of a &#x27;blame game&#x27; and vowed measures to protect citizens, signaling hardening language from Islamabad</li></ul><blockquote>Regrettably, the Afghan side gave no assurances, kept deviating from the core issue and resorted to blame game, deflection and ruses, - Attaullah Tarar</blockquote><h3>Perspectives:</h3><ul><li>Pakistan government: Pakistan said talks failed to produce a &#x27;workable solution&#x27; and accused the Afghan side of supporting anti‑Pakistan terrorists, demanding action against militants . (<a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1951912/pak-afghan-talks-in-istanbul-failed-to-bring-about-any-workable-solution-says-information-minister'>Dawn</a>)</li><li>Afghan Taliban authorities: The Taliban government has consistently denied allegations that it harbours groups that attack Pakistan, rejecting Islamabad&#x27;s charges . (<a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/pakistan-afghanistan-playing-blame-game-peace-talks-failed'>The New Arab</a>)</li><li>Independent analysts: Analysts warn that the breakdown and unresolved demands to dismantle the TTP increase the risk of broader escalation between the neighbours . (<a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/29/last-ditch-push-pakistan-afghanistan-talks-falter-amid-deep-mistrust'>Al Jazeera</a>)</li></ul><h3>Sources:</h3><ul><li><a href='https://www.rferl.org/a/afghanistan-pakistan-taliban-negotiations-clashes-border/33575282.html'>Pakistan Says Peace Talks With Afghan Taliban Fail To Find &#x27;Workable Solution&#x27;</a> - rferl.org</li><li><a href='https://www.thehindu.com/news/international/pakistan-confirms-talks-with-afghanistan-failed-accuses-kabul-of-backtracking-on-commitments/article70215420.ece'>Pakistan confirms talks with Afghanistan failed, accuses Kabul of backtracking on commitments</a> - thehindu.com</li><li><a href='https://www.newarab.com/news/pakistan-afghanistan-playing-blame-game-peace-talks-failed'>Pakistan: Afghanistan playing &#x27;blame game&#x27;, peace talks &#x27;failed&#x27;</a> - newarab.com</li><li><a href='https://www.firstpost.com/explainers/afghanistan-pakistan-border-talks-turkey-qatar-what-next-13945959.html'>Could failed Afghanistan-Pakistan peace reignite the conflict?</a> - firstpost.com</li><li><a href='https://www.aljazeera.com/news/2025/10/29/last-ditch-push-pakistan-afghanistan-talks-falter-amid-deep-mistrust'>‘Last-ditch push’: Pakistan-Afghanistan talks falter amid deep mistrust</a> - aljazeera.com</li><li><a href='https://www.dawn.com/news/1951912/pak-afghan-talks-in-istanbul-failed-to-bring-about-any